<h1>Quick Markdown</h1>

<p> Automatically format an article's <b>bold</b> and <i>italic</i> words in the markdown language used in the Byliner Admin. (<%= mail_to("jj5201@gmail.com", "Report Bugs", :subject => "Markdown App Bug(s)") %>) </p> 


<div id="ocr" style="height:500px;width:550px;float:left; padding-right:100px">
	<h2>For .rtf files: </h2>
	<ol>
		<li>In gmail, scroll down to the appropriate file attachment & <b>Click "View as HTML"</b></li>
		<li>In the html view, <b>Select All & Copy </b>
		<li><b>Paste</b> into a <u>word processor</u></li> and <b>Save with a .html extensension</b><br></li>(<%= link_to("Need a word processor?", "http://www.libreoffice.org/", :target => "_blank") %>)
		<li>Open your new .html file in a <u>text editor</u>, <b>Select All & Copy </b></li>
		<li><b>Paste</b> into the box below & <b>Click Submit</b>!</li>
	</ol> 




	<%= form_for(@harvest) do |f| %>
	 

		<div class="field">

			<%= f.text_area :raw_text, size: "70x15", placeholder: "Paste the source code here..." %>

		</div>



	<%= f.submit "Submit", class: "btn btn-large btn-primary" %>
	<% end %>
</div>

